> A customer favourite, this Presto Prawn and Mushroom Linguine is a tried-and-tested recipe that always wins with a crowd.

Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} widthways.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Drain the @king prawns{225%g}.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and prawns.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until the prawns are cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once the prawns are cooked, lower the heat. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

When the pasta has ~{4%minutes} left, add the broccoli to the same pan and cook for the remaining time.

Once the pasta and broccoli are cooked, reserve some of the pasta water, then drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with oil and stir through to prevent it sticking.

Stir the @reserved pasta water{100%ml}, @creme fraiche{150%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g} into the mushrooms and prawns, simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked pasta, broccoli and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} to the sauce and gently toss to coat.

Add another splash of water if the sauce is a bit thick. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Share the prawn and mushroom linguine between your bowls. Enjoy!